    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Slice your <strong>sweet potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into discs (approx. 0.5cm thick)</p><p>Add the <strong>sweet potato discs</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 10-12 min until softened slightly</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-mince-and-sweet-potato-lasagne-with-mozzarella/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail, and finely dice your<strong> carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped onion </strong>and<strong> diced carrot </strong>and cook for 4 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-mince-and-sweet-potato-lasagne-with-mozzarella/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain your <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella </strong>into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Once the onion and carrot have softened, increase the heat to high then add your <strong>mince</strong> to the pan</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until browned all over, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-mince-and-sweet-potato-lasagne-with-mozzarella/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the mince is cooking, boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>dried oregano </strong>and a pinch of<strong> sugar</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-mince-and-sweet-potato-lasagne-with-mozzarella/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mince has browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>to the pan and cook for 30 secs, then add the<strong> tomato stock</strong> with a generous grind of<strong> black pepper </strong>and cook for 5-7 min or until thickened to a rag\u00f9-like consistency and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your<strong> rag\u00f9</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, add a pot to a medium heat with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, once hot, add 20g <span class=\"text-purple\">[30g] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms \u2013 this is your <strong>roux</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-mince-and-sweet-potato-lasagne-with-mozzarella/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Gradually whisk 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> into the roux, a little at a time and cook for 2-3 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p><p>Remove from the heat, season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>b\u00e9chamel sauce</strong></p><p>While the b\u00e9chamel is cooking, combine your <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> dressing</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-mince-and-sweet-potato-lasagne-with-mozzarella/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Layer the bottom of an <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>with <strong>half</strong> of the<strong> sweet potato discs </strong>followed by<strong> half </strong>of the<strong> rag\u00fa</strong>,<strong> half </strong>of the <strong>b\u00e9chamel sauce </strong>and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>torn mozzarella</strong></p><p>Repeat this process until you end up with a final layer of the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>b\u00e9chamel sauce</strong></p><p>Top with the<strong> remaining</strong> <strong>torn</strong> <strong>mozzarella</strong> and cook in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and bubbling \u2013 this is your<strong> mince & sweet potato lasagne</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-mince-and-sweet-potato-lasagne-with-mozzarella/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> mince & sweet potato lasagne</strong> with the<strong> salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle the <strong>dressing </strong>over the salad</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
